2. The ISO 26262 Challenge for AI


ISO 26262 requires:

Requirement Stochastic AI ST‑T1024
Determinism ❌ Probabilistic outputs ✅ FSM‑enforced, WCET ≤ 800 ns
Traceability ❌ Black‑box decision making ✅ Fully auditable state transitions
Freedom from Interference ❌ Shared resources, unpredictable contention ✅ Tile‑based isolation, power gating
ASIL Decomposition ❌ Cannot be decomposed deterministically ✅ Safety goals mapped to deterministic logic

The functional safety standards that govern automotive systems were developed for deterministic software: code that processes inputs through defined logic and produces outputs that can be formally specified. Stochastic AI does not meet this criterion.

